<br>
Kate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luvthatdyl>LuvThatDyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/17/03 12:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Is Kate Weird?</span><hr size=1> LOL.  No, you aren't weird.  You are just observant.  Part of your observation may have been due to the fact that you were constantly cognizant of the problems over there, and part of it may have been an accurate observation.  It is easy to take for granted what we have here in this country, and whenever something bad happens, it is reflected in the mannerisms of society.  When we moved to Colorado, my dh noticed the difference in traffic patterns the day after the Broncos played a game.  No joke.  Traffic was always worse the day after they lost.  When they were in the Superbowl, there was a state of elation in the area, and it was almost like a holiday.  If people can act so different over something as trivial as football, then political strife would really make a huge difference.  <br>
